div.p:
There was a goodly consecration when the dānavas, Māli, Sumāli, who on seeing him became attached to Rāghava’s foe, made it; 
              thence arise the adored name of the god Suvarṇamahākṣi. Sumāli’s name came to the currently attached to the town. 
              On this account how do they praise it within the bounds of the surrounding land of Kūṇḍi.
